text: Entering midway in this movie I slowly became disappointed. The beginning was intriguing as it was scientific and dived into what truly could happen. I love The OA and The Discovery as they seemed possible (except for The OA at a certain point, no spoilers). But this movie turned into a horror film, which I did not expect. I wanted it to explore deeper into the science or provide a logical premise that is new and surprising so that we can leave the movies in awe and mindful curiosity. For example, Interstellar left me blown away as I am into astronomy and physics and quantum physics and all that was presented seemed plausible. A movie like that makes me curious and it seems even feasible in its science. I was just hoping to walk away from this movie with a different mindset and insight into the important question of what happens to our consciousness after we die.

text: While I absolutely LOVED Flatliners, people should understand one thing about real near death experiences. All seeing the SAME earth equals One Reality. Most seeing different places and different things equals Lies being told to the people who experience it. People who haven't had one yet, if you do, please ask what the universe is and why others aren't seeing the same thing you are. Please ask what the point of this experiment is.  There can't be a world full of liars who are all just claiming different stories.  Think about it.  Beth
